Kansas, a predominately red state, has had a bill PASS THROUGH THE HOUSE and is awaiting approval from the Senate that will allow for businesses, establishments, law enforcement and health care systems to deny access, entry, and assistance to gay couples that, through a loophole, extends to any individual that is perceived to be gay in the state. This bill is UNLAWFUL [Emergency Medical Treatment and Active Labor Act] and should be brought to the attention of the Obama Administration before it can harm anyone in the state. This bill has the power to potentially kill individuals due to the fact that police & hospitals can deny their services. Strike it!

One article that explains the bill;
http://www.slate.com/blogs/outward/2014/02/13/kansas_anti_gay_segregation_bill_is_an_abomination.html

